data.title: Individual, group and regional team titles awarded at 2023 Rhythmic Development Program National Championships • USA Gymnastics
data.meta_description: Regions 1, 6 and 4 topped the regional team standings as national titles were awarded at the 2023 Rhythmic Development Program National Championships over the weekend in West Palm Beach, Fla.
data.text:
Individual Results: Level 6 | Level 7 | Level 8

Group Results: Beginner | Intermediate | Advanced

Region Team Results: Level 6 | Level 7 | Level 8

Regions 1, 6 and 4 topped the regional team standings as national titles were awarded at the 2023 Rhythmic Development Program National Championships over the weekend in West Palm Beach, Fla.

In regional competition, Region 1 posted a combined 521.750 to top the Level 6 standings ahead of Regions 4 (514.850) and 6 (501.100). In Level 7 competition, Region 6 led with a combined 615.150. Region 1 was second (608.550) and Region 4 third (603.550). Region 4 claimed the team title in Level 8 competition with a 648.000, with Regions 6 and 5 taking second and third with scores of 599.950 and 565.150, respectively.

Individual and group all-around winners were also determined during weekend’s event. Champions, as well as any apparatus titles they won, are listed below by level.

Individual
